Judas's Note:

I've lots of blurays... lots, I know what looks phenomenal on bluray and what doesn't. There aren't many movies that look quite as bad as The Hurt Locker, it's really VERY disappointing. So this doesn't make encoding it anywhere near being remotely a &quot;pleasure&quot; because it frankly just looks fuzzy all the time, and ultra grainy. There is a non-stop amount of judder/movement for the film on bluray, this doesn't exactly make encoding easy at all to begin with, but the image quality on bluray was just terrible too. Looks like they filmed it with a potatoe and then upscaled it to 1080p. Either way, don't be surprised if you think it looks terrible. I even encoded it 3 times with various settings just to see if I could improve something somewhere, but in the end, I just had to suck it up. I wasn't even going to bother uploading it, but I've had numerous requests for it.
